.TH "t4_tp_wr_bits_indirect" 9 "t4_tp_wr_bits_indirect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4_tp_wr_bits_indirect \- set/clear bits in an indirect TP register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" t4_tp_wr_bits_indirect
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "addr" 12
the indirect TP register address
.IP "mask" 12
specifies the field within the register to modify
.IP "val" 12
new value for the field

Sets a field of an indirect TP register to the given value.
